Toni Braxton attends WE tv's "Braxton Family Values" Season 6 Premiere at The Doheny Room on April 02, 2019 in West Hollywood, California. JOHANNESBURG - Grammy award-winning singer Toni Braxton is bringing her As Long As I Live tour to South Africa. The tour, presented by Glen 21 Entertainment in association with McDonalds and powered by Kaya FM, will include shows in Johannesburg and Cape Town. Braxton is commemorating her 25th anniversary in the music industry this year. The Johannesburg show will take place on 9 November at the Ticketpro Dome and in Cape Town she will perform at the Grand Arena, Grandwest Casino on 12 November. Tickets range from R650 to R2880 and are available at Ticketpros.co.za.